}}'''劳斯伽姆北部石柱遗迹'''（Lothagam North Pillar Site）是[[肯尼亚|肯尼亚]][[图尔卡纳湖|图尔卡纳湖]]西侧的一处考古遗址，其历史可追溯到新石器时代。它是一个公共墓地，由公元前3000年至公元前2300年之间生活在该地区的牧民建造<ref name="Hildebrand">{{Cite journal|title=A monumental cemetery built by eastern Africa's first herders near Lake Turkana, Kenya|last=Hildebrand|first=Elisabeth|date=2018|journal=PNAS|issue=36|doi=10.1073/pnas.1721975115|volume=115|pages=8942–8947|pmc=6130363|pmid=30127016|display-authors=etal}}</ref><ref name="gizmodo">{{Cite web|title=Ancient Cemetery Packed With Hundreds of Bodies Discovered in Kenya|url=https://gizmodo.com/ancient-cemetery-packed-with-hundreds-of-bodies-discove-1828467180|author=Dvorsky|date=2018-08-20|first=George}}</ref><ref name="natgeo">{{Cite web|title=Ancient Riches Discovered at Mysterious Burial Monument|url=https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/2018/08/news-ancient-pillar-monument-burial-mound-africa|author=Maya Wei-Haas|date=2018-08-20|work=National Geographic}}</ref>。它被认为是[[东非|东非]]最大和最早的[[墳場|墳場]]<ref name="livescience">{{Cite web|title=Massive, Ancient Stone Monument in Kenya Held More Than 500 Bodies, 400 Gerbil Teeth|url=https://www.livescience.com/63397-kenya-ancient-cemetery-monument-lothagam.html|author=Specktor|date=2018-08-22|first=Brandon|publisher=Live Science}}</ref>。

